      Description copied from interface: CommonQueryContract
      Obtain the query timeout in seconds.

    • setTimeout

      public CommonQueryContract setTimeout(int timeout)
      Description copied from interface: CommonQueryContract
      Set the query timeout in seconds.

      Any value set here is eventually passed directly along to the JDBC statement, which expressly disallows negative values. So negative values should be avoided as a general rule.

      A value of zero indicates no timeout.

      Specified by:
